race.description: Royal Australian Signals Centenary Class 1 Handicap
race.comment: JUDGE JENNI (5) has been racing well since joining the new yard, narrowly missing first Tassie run then stepping up to a mile last time and getting off the mark. Going well and worth following up. REGAL HUNTER (1) made debut with a narrow loss over 1200m the stepped straight to 1400m and was off the mark with an on speed maiden win. Has upside and should take catching over the mile. HENLEY EXTREME (4) is racing well, beating JUDGE JENNI two back before finishing runner-up behind Halen latest. Will give a sight again. THIN RED LINE (8) is struggling to get a win on the board but recent runs have been sound. Hit the line nicely for fourth last time and if they go hard early here will be winding up late. FLORENCE GLASS (3) will no doubt be aiming for longer races over the summer but is fitter for two trials and did win only try at the mile. Keep safe.
